FBIS3-32370 "drlat025_e_94012" FBIS-LAT-94-025 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Feb 1994 CENTRAL AMERICA Costa Rica Report on First Statements by President-Elect Figueres PA0702060994 San Jose Radio Reloj in Spanish 0524 GMT 7 Feb 94 PA0702060994 San Jose Radio Reloj Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Report by Mitzi Madrigal] [Text] We are broadcasting directly from the Jose Figueres Ferrer Liberationist House where new President Jose Maria Figueres Olsen has given his first impromptu speech indicating that as president-elect of Costa Rica he will continue with the promises made during the election campaign. He promised that he will help those most needy sectors of Costa Rica and also reiterated that as of tomorrow we must all stand under the same white, blue, and red flag to fight for Costa Rica's cause. Let us now listen to statements by President-elect Jose Maria Figueres Olsen's here in front of the Green Balcony. [Begin Figueres recording] ... the future is ahead. The future, hope, and expectation lie ahead with National Liberation once again in the government. [applause and music] I would also like to express my appreciation to many men and women. I would like to thank [word indistinct], my lifelong companion, who has supported me and helped me transcend tough and difficult moments. I would also like to thank [words indistinct]. [end recording] We just listened to part of the statements made by Jose Maria Figueres Olsen who was chosen today as the new Costa Rican president. Tomorrow, during our first newscast we will be providing more details related to this election process and statements made during the day by President-elect Jose Maria Olsen.
